headline: AutoZone's third quarter profit falls 6.6% on currency headwinds
summary: Its domestic same-store sales rose 5% in the third quarter ended May 10, compared to a flat growth last year, aided by sustained demand from commercial customers.  The industry has also been dealing with higher supply chain costs due to U.S. President Donald Trump's tariffs, while consumers have also tightened their budgets amid concerns of a recession.  Trump's shifting tariff policies and trade war rhetoric have also led to volatility in global markets, and put pressure on the U.S. dollar.
